# Todo Console App - Phase 1

**Hackathon Project**: Evolution of Todo - Phase 1 (Console Application)

## Overview

A command-line todo application with in-memory storage featuring 5 Basic Level operations:
1. View all tasks
2. Add new task
3. Mark task complete/incomplete
4. Update task details
5. Delete task

## Requirements

- Python 3.13+
- UV package manager

## Setup

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/Aliladla/hackathon2phase1.git
cd hackathon2phase1

# Install dependencies
uv sync

# Run the application
uv run python -m todo
```

## Usage

The application provides an interactive menu:

```
=== Todo App ===
1. View all tasks
2. Add new task
3. Mark task complete/incomplete
4. Update task
5. Delete task
6. Exit

Enter choice (1-6):
```

## Testing

```bash
# Run all tests
uv run pytest

# Run with coverage
uv run pytest --cov=src/todo --cov-report=html
```

## Architecture

- **Domain Layer** (`src/todo/domain/`): Core business logic (Task entity, TaskManager)
- **Storage Layer** (`src/todo/storage/`): In-memory repository
- **CLI Layer** (`src/todo/cli/`): User interface and display

## Features

- ✅ Add tasks with title and description
- ✅ View all tasks with status indicators
- ✅ Mark tasks as complete/incomplete
- ✅ Update task details
- ✅ Delete tasks
- ✅ Input validation and error handling

## Limitations (Phase 1)

- In-memory storage only (tasks lost on exit)
- Single-user application
- No persistence to disk

## Next Phases

- **Phase 2**: Full-stack web application with database persistence
- **Phase 3**: AI-powered chatbot interface

